    "client_msg_id": "7ec1004f-6eff-4758-9bbd-bb75b820bc13",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "We’re experimenting with different ways of summarising information visually.\nThis a simple one where we get ‘named entities’, group and lay them out as a tree.\n(other categories can be added of course based on anything that an LLM can produce)\n\n<https://youtu.be/zwEIYtG_KrI>\n\nTo me at least there are couple of interesting things in this space:\n- *interactions*\n  - pagination (done!), sorting, filtering, (re-) moving of the nodes\n  - bidirectional connection to the source (e.g. navigating to a particular mention in the parent block,) and canvas (drag and drop of the nodes to expand on canvas)—cf. the video\n- *multiple sources + analysis &amp; comparison*\n  - e.g. a graph that answers the question of what are some common themes, ideas, entities in two pieces of information (e.g. a video lecture and a webpage)\n- *tools for extending the graph*\n  - by search\n  - by generative AI\n  - by custom/manual annotations\n\nI would of course be very grateful for comments on any of the above :pray:\n\nWonderful weekend to you all :tropical_drink:",
    "user": "UQ2P2BYJU",
    "ts": "1694883292.945819",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "C7BI",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "We’re experimenting with different ways of summarising information visually.\nThis a simple one where we get ‘named entities’, group and lay them out as a tree.\n(other categories can be added of course based on anything that an LLM can produce)\n\n"
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://youtu.be/zwEIYtG_KrI"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n\nTo me at least there are couple of interesting things in this space:\n- "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "interactions",
                "style": {
                  "bold": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n  - pagination (done!), sorting, filtering, (re-) moving of the nodes\n  - bidirectional connection to the source (e.g. navigating to a particular mention in the parent block,) and canvas (drag and drop of the nodes to expand on canvas)—cf. the video\n- "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "multiple sources + analysis & comparison",
                "style": {
                  "bold": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n  - e.g. a graph that answers the question of what are some common themes, ideas, entities in two pieces of information (e.g. a video lecture and a webpage)\n- "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "tools for extending the graph",
                "style": {
                  "bold": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n  - by search\n  - by generative AI\n  - by custom/manual annotations\n\nI would of course be very grateful for comments on any of the above "
              },
              {
                "type": "emoji",
                "name": "pray",
                "unicode": "1f64f"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n\nWonderful weekend to you all "
              },
              {
                "type": "emoji",
                "name": "tropical_drink",
                "unicode": "1f379"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
